{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"254c1813-f597-4aae-808a-d7648b0ee992","content":"The directory appears to be empty — there's no workflow file here for me to modify. That said, here's exactly what you need to change to switch from `secrets.NUGET_API_KEY` to **NuGet trusted publishing (OIDC)**:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Configure NuGet.org\n\nOn [nuget.org](https://www.nuget.org), go to your package → **Manage** → **Trusted publishers** and add a GitHub Actions policy specifying your **repository owner**, **repository name**, **workflow file name**, and optionally an **environment**.\n\n### 2. Update your GitHub Actions workflow\n\n**a) Add `id-token: write` permission** (required for OIDC):\n\n```yaml\npermissions:\n  id-token: write   # request OIDC token\n  contents: read\n```\n\n**b) Replace the `dotnet nuget push` step.** Remove the API key and use `--source` with the trusted publisher endpoint:\n\n```yaml\n# Before\n- run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json --api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }}\n\n# After\n- uses: actions/setup-dotnet@v4\n  with:\n    dotnet-version: '8.x'     # or your target version\n\n- run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\nThe key difference: **no `--api-key` flag**. The `setup-dotnet@v4` action automatically acquires an OIDC token and authenticates when `id-token: write` is set.\n\n### 3. (Recommended) Use a GitHub environment\n\nLock it down by requiring an environment (e.g., `nuget-publish`):\n\n```yaml\njobs:\n  publish:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    environment: nuget-publish   # matches what you registered on nuget.org\n    permissions:\n      id-token: write\n      contents: read\n```\n\n### 4. Remove the secret\n\nOnce verified, delete `NUGET_API_KEY` from your repo's **Settings → Secrets**.\n\n---\n\n**Summary of changes:**\n| Area | Old | New |\n|---|---|---|\n| Auth | `secrets.NUGET_API_KEY` | OIDC via `id-token: write` |\n| Push command | `--api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }}` | No `--api-key` flag |\n| NuGet.org config | API key | Trusted publisher policy |\n| setup-dotnet | Any version | `v4+` (OIDC-aware) |\n\nWant me to create or update a specific workflow file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"cebe2aa6-3d5e-48fc-be01-a13ef8331bac","outputTokens":657},"id":"6e1076e4-0363-4edc-b562-c6506951ddab","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:41:57.827Z","parentId":"ef9df179-c875-4649-a58d-37b0124a5a2c"}
